HEADWORD: Burgoo
<hw>Bur"goo</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>burgood</ets> yeast, perh. fr. W. <ets>burym</ets> yeast +
<ets>cawl</ets> cabbage, gruel.]</ety> <def>A kind of oatmeal pudding,
or thick gruel, used by seamen.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>burgout</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

